Dialogue: 0,0:00:-01.-01,0:00:00.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Inherited will...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.62,0:00:03.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The tide of the times...\NPeople's dreams...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:03.49,0:00:06.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,These things cannot be stopped.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:06.33,0:00:09.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,As long as people\Nseek the answer of freedom,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:09.43,0:00:17.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,these things will never cease to be!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:20.98,0:00:27.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I only believe in the future --\NI don't care if anyone laughs
Dialogue: 0,0:00:27.05,0:00:32.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That racing passion makes you shine
Dialogue: 0,0:00:32.56,0:00:38.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's too bright,\Nbut I want to gaze at it
Dialogue: 0,0:00:38.56,0:00:42.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I sense "aesthetics" somewhere
Dialogue: 0,0:00:42.06,0:00:45.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm really really stuck on you
Dialogue: 0,0:00:45.37,0:00:51.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I follow, follow in the footsteps\Nof a dream that resembles no one
Dialogue: 0,0:00:52.01,0:00:55.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Until I dramatically get it
Dialogue: 0,0:00:55.31,0:01:03.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Believe In Wonderland!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:04.22,0:01:10.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm going to catch, catch the shape\Nof a dream no one can see
Dialogue: 0,0:01:10.43,0:01:16.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm going to go with you,\Nso passionate feelings
Dialogue: 0,0:01:16.47,0:01:19.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't really\Nneed everything to add up
Dialogue: 0,0:01:19.54,0:01:22.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Rather than run-of-the-mill daily life,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:22.71,0:01:26.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,run for paradise instead
Dialogue: 0,0:01:26.31,0:01:34.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Believe In Wonderland!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:36.05,0:01:38.97,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,"Yuba"              "Nanohana"   "Katorea"
Dialogue: 0,0:01:38.99,0:01:43.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Three years have passed since\Na single drop of rain fell
Dialogue: 0,0:01:43.19,0:01:45.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,in the kingdom of oases.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:45.13,0:01:50.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Seeing hope beyond turmoil,\Nthe people took up weapons.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:50.07,0:01:53.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The burning land is now\Nenveloped by a sad bellowing
Dialogue: 0,0:01:53.67,0:01:57.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and a mighty swell.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:57.38,0:02:00.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In the Alabasta port town of Nanohana,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:00.28,0:02:03.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Luffy reunited with his\Nolder brother, Ace.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:03.95,0:02:07.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ace demonstrates the power\Nof the Flame-Flame Fruit.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:07.52,0:02:09.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,With Ace by their side,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.45,0:02:17.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,the party follows the Sandora\NRiver upstream toward Yuba.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.03,0:02:27.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"Erumalu, the City of Green,\Nand the Kung Fu Dugongs!"
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.38,0:02:35.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,--Halt!\N--What business do you have here?!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.81,0:02:38.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Please! Let us see the king!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.08,0:02:41.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How long is this civil war\Ngoing to keep up?!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.15,0:02:44.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,With this civil war and drought,\Nwe have nothing left to eat!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.72,0:02:47.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Please help my child!\NThere's no milk left!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.62,0:02:49.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Stop! Quit pushing!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.19,0:02:51.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We can't let you through!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.29,0:02:59.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,--Let us speak with the king!\N--You want us to just die, then?!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.15,0:03:14.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,--Hey! Say somethin', will ya?!\N--Are you just gonna abandon us?!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.12,0:03:16.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And you call yourself a king?!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.69,0:03:19.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why, you! Don't you dare\Ninsult His Royal Highness!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.09,0:03:26.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Cease that at once, guards!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.46,0:03:27.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.00,0:03:34.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My lack of strength has put you\Nthrough such unbearable suffering.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.24,0:03:36.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Those who wish to speak,\Nplease come inside
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.31,0:03:38.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and tell me of your qualms.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.87,0:03:45.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,All I can do now is share your\Nsuffering as if it were my own as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.92,0:03:52.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I ask that you endure a little more.\NI will return calm to this kingdom.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.22,0:03:56.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Even at the expense of my life!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.56,0:03:59.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Father! Someone set this up!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.40,0:04:07.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's clear that someone is trying\Nto throw this kingdom into ruin!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.34,0:04:17.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I hope you're all right...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.48,0:04:23.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Where are you now,\Nand what are you doing, Vivi?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.72,0:04:27.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Tea's ready. Come on up to the kitchen.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.29,0:04:34.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you, Sanji-san!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.86,0:04:39.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Heya! I'm Captain Rice Ball Usopp!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.10,0:04:41.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh! And who are you?!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.40,0:04:44.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm a riceman!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.87,0:04:47.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Quit playing with our food!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.51,0:04:49.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If you got free time,\Ngo wash dishes or something!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.35,0:04:53.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Geez! I need to finish our packed\Nmeals before we cross the river!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.22,0:04:54.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Need a hand?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.72,0:05:00.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, no. You are a guest on board.\NJust sit back and relax.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.96,0:05:03.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.86,0:05:08.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't wash the dishes\Nin that mop bucket!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.66,0:05:16.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What a nice breeze!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.54,0:05:23.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Nami-san. I'd like to land\Nthe ship here for a moment...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.48,0:05:24.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Eh? What for?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.01,0:05:27.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I have an important task for Karoo.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.78,0:05:35.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Karoo?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.29,0:05:39.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Karoo. I want you to go to\NAlubarna Palace on your own
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.09,0:05:41.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and deliver this letter to my father.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.83,0:05:45.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I've written down everything\NIgaram and I learned
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.60,0:05:49.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,about Crocodile and\NBaroque Works' schemes.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.27,0:05:57.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And that I've returned to Alabasta\Nalive with supportive friends.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.11,0:06:05.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Can you do it? You'll have to\Ncross the desert on your own.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.79,0:06:10.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Listen. You have to drink your\Nwater with care in the desert.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.56,0:06:12.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Karoo! Good luck!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.66,0:06:20.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now let my father know\Nthis kingdom can be saved!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.27,0:06:28.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Drink your water with care!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.54,0:06:31.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Karoo... Thank you...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.88,0:06:36.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I knew Crocodile, one of the Seven\NWarlords, was in this country...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.65,0:06:41.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But a pirate trying to steal a kingdom?\NThat sounds like a bad joke.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.29,0:06:44.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A pirate dropping anchor in\None spot and settling down?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.96,0:06:48.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't tell me he's trying\Nto usurp the throne.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.13,0:06:49.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Alright! Let's set sail!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.97,0:06:52.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hold on! I'm not on board yet!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.10,0:06:56.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There could be another side\Nto this takeover thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.14,0:06:57.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Another side?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.34,0:07:05.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Some sort of deeper goal...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.15,0:07:09.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Alabasta, the kingdom of sand...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.55,0:07:11.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Even if you build cities\Natop the sandy earth
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.55,0:07:13.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and exist there for\Nthousands of years,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.49,0:07:17.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,the desert will always be\Nfilled with the stench of death.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.56,0:07:24.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,From its very inception, this land\Nhas embraced the shadow of death.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.87,0:07:29.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I've just received word that the\NBillions' ships stationed in Nanohana
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.97,0:07:33.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,have all been wiped out by someone...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.31,0:07:41.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm having this verified as we speak.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.35,0:07:45.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There are more replacements for\Nthe Billions than we even need.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.62,0:07:51.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A single drop of water spilled in the\Ndesert is no obstacle for my plan.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.56,0:07:56.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But, if anyone who would\Ndare defy me has appeared...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.53,0:07:59.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,crush them.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.37,0:08:01.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Understood.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.00,0:08:10.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I've already sent the Lizard\NRunners to contact the others.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.31,0:08:15.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Excellent.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.78,0:08:17.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We're finally here!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.59,0:08:21.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We're finally going into the desert!\NI bet it'll be hot...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.56,0:08:25.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,--It gets over 50 C in the daytime!\N--Eh?! It does?!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.53,0:08:28.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What happened, Nami-san?!\NWhere did your dancer outfit go?!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.86,0:08:32.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Aah! Not you too, Vivi-chan!\NWhy are you dressed like that?!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.30,0:08:38.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In the desert, any exposed skin\Nwill wind up terribly sunburned!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.17,0:08:41.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is terrible... My dancer girls...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.14,0:08:42.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Put this on, Luffy-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.21,0:08:43.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay! Thank you!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.78,0:08:51.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,--Let's get ready to disembark.\N--Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.99,0:09:00.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay! Let's land!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.83,0:09:08.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's that?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.77,0:09:11.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,--Turtles?\N--Aren't those seals?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.07,0:09:13.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Kung Fu Dugongs!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.88,0:09:16.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"If you wanna come on shore,\Nyou'll have to beat me first!"
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.28,0:09:18.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"Or else go back to\Nthe other shore, cowards!"
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.01,0:09:22.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is what he says.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.55,0:09:25.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I can't sit quietly by when\Nsomeone calls me a coward!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.39,0:09:29.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,--Let's do it!\N--Wait! Usopp-san!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.12,0:09:33.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Kung Fu Dugongs are strong!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.86,0:09:41.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,--One is winning over there!\N--Winning is bad, too!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.64,0:09:43.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.87,0:09:45.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's a Kung Fu Dugong rule
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.64,0:09:48.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,that if someone loses,\Nthey become the winner's pupil!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.54,0:09:52.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's very martial arts-ish.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.48,0:09:54.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The number of pupils just went up!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.55,0:09:56.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Alright, everyone! After me!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.69,0:09:58.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Stance!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.35,0:10:00.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No! Like this!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.89,0:10:03.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah! Now go like this!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.63,0:10:06.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's it! Like this!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.06,0:10:08.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Like this! Like this!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.17,0:10:16.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Like this!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.62,0:10:28.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Alright! Let's set out for Yuba!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.52,0:10:31.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hold on, now!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.42,0:10:33.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you bringing them with us?!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.52,0:10:35.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You can't, Luffy!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.06,0:10:41.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The Dugongs can't cross the desert...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.26,0:10:43.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So cute...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.60,0:10:47.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know why, but I feel like\Nwe're doing something very sad...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.07,0:10:49.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Me, too. What should we do?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.94,0:10:51.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I know!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.11,0:10:52.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's see here...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.01,0:10:54.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What're you doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.85,0:10:56.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Here!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.04,0:11:01.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You can have this! So stay here, okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.12,0:11:09.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,--Help!\N--Chopper!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.12,0:11:13.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,See ya!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.50,0:11:16.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey now, Luffy! Do you understand\Nthe current situation?!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.50,0:11:19.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They said they were coming with me,\Nso why couldn't we let them?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.47,0:11:23.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We couldn't go to any city with\Nthat big of a group! You're so dumb!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.67,0:11:24.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Honestly!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.37,0:11:27.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We would've been in big trouble\Nhad Chopper not persuaded them!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.34,0:11:30.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah! They kept saying,\N"We'll accompany you!"
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.65,0:11:33.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They really would've come if\Nwe hadn't given them food!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.92,0:11:38.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sheesh! Thanks to you, our food\Nsupply's gotten a lot smaller!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.55,0:11:46.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,--He knows how to cause trouble.\N--That's for sure!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.37,0:11:55.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,--What's this?\N--Is this the town of Yuba?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.67,0:11:57.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.31,0:12:01.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is Erumalu. It used to be\Nknown as the City of Green...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.74,0:12:03.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,City of Green?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.01,0:12:06.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The sight of this town\Nexplains everything.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.28,0:12:10.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What the Baroque Works organization\Nhas done to this country...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.22,0:12:18.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What the people of Alabasta\Nare going through...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.66,0:12:24.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wow! There's nothing here at all!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.90,0:12:28.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. It's a ghost town now,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.97,0:12:34.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but up until just recently, it was\Na thriving city full of greenery!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.28,0:12:37.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This place was?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.18,0:12:43.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Rain was always scarce, but even so,\Nthe city was able to manage
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.62,0:12:46.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,by saving every last drop\Nof rainwater it could.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.29,0:12:48.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But, for three years now,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.72,0:12:53.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,not a single drop of rain has\Nfallen in any part of this country.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.16,0:12:55.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,--For three years?!\N--That long?!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.66,0:12:59.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But even without rain, what\Nabout the river we just crossed?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.97,0:13:03.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah! Couldn't they just pipe\Nwater in from that big river?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.81,0:13:10.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The answer to that is up ahead.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.68,0:13:13.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Never in the thousands of\Nyears of Alabasta's history
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.88,0:13:16.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,has the rain stopped completely.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.82,0:13:22.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But, there was one place where\Nthe rain fell more than usual...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.29,0:13:30.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Alubarna, the capital.\NThe city with the king's palace...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.19,0:13:50.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The people called it\Nthe King's Miracle.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.49,0:13:53.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Until what happened\Nthat day, at least...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.66,0:14:01.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Lower the cargo!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.14,0:14:05.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's falling over!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.87,0:14:08.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Look out!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.87,0:14:11.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey! Are you alright?!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.81,0:14:13.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, no! This is bad!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.98,0:14:17.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We were supposed to deliver\Nthis to King Cobra in Alubarna!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.68,0:14:20.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What is this green powder?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.45,0:14:21.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.72,0:14:25.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,H-How should we know?!\NWe're only following your king's orders!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.69,0:14:28.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,--Right?\N--We're just couriers!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.23,0:14:32.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Run!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.29,0:14:35.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wait... Could this be?!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.36,0:14:38.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Dance Powder?!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.07,0:14:39.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You've heard of it?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.90,0:14:43.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. It's also known as\N"Rain-Summoning Powder."
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.84,0:14:45.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Rain-summoning?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.17,0:14:47.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'd only heard stories about it,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.48,0:14:51.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but a researcher in a country\Nwhere it doesn't rain created it.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.88,0:14:56.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,By creating a misty smoke from it\Nand letting it rise into the sky,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.96,0:14:59.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,you can artificially cause it to rain.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.89,0:15:02.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's what Dance Powder is.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.46,0:15:04.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh! I get it!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.76,0:15:06.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You mean that mystery powder!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.46,0:15:10.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I ate some a while back!\NIt tastes really bad!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.67,0:15:12.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It isn't food.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.87,0:15:15.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's for making rain.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.14,0:15:19.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?! You think I'm lying,\Ndon't you?! Hey, you!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.54,0:15:23.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hold on! Wouldn't something like\Nthat be perfect for this country?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.58,0:15:27.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,As the name suggests, the country\Nthat developed Dance Powder
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.22,0:15:30.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,was almost happy enough\Nto dance at first.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.32,0:15:33.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But there was a big catch:
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.96,0:15:37.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,the neighboring country had a drought.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.49,0:15:38.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Understand?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.56,0:15:43.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Dance Powder quickly and\Nartificially matures clouds
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.53,0:15:48.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,that would normally grow into\Nrain clouds further downwind
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.34,0:15:50.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and causes them to rain.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.51,0:15:51.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.11,0:15:52.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, I get it!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.14,0:15:57.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It steals rain that would've normally\Ngone to a neighboring country!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.21,0:15:59.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Eventually, war broke out\Nbetween the two countries
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.98,0:16:03.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and many lives were lost as a result.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.12,0:16:05.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ever since, the World Government\Nhas put a worldwide ban
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.89,0:16:08.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,on the production and\Npossession of Dance Powder.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.16,0:16:12.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Powder that can bring both\Nhappiness and dread when used...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.06,0:16:16.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When all that Dance Powder was\Nbrought into the port town,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.03,0:16:19.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Alabasta was in the middle of\Na strange weather phenomenon
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.03,0:16:23.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,where rain fell nowhere but in\Nthe town where the king lived.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.07,0:16:25.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We haven't had a single drop of rain
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.67,0:16:28.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,because the king's been\Nusing Dance Powder!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.31,0:16:31.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Alubarna's rain wasn't a miracle at all!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.71,0:16:37.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's all because of the king\Nthat we're parched and starving!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.19,0:16:40.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hold on, Vivi! That means\Nyour dad is the bad guy here!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.36,0:16:42.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You idiot! He was framed!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.72,0:16:45.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Vivi-chan's father would\Nnever do any such thing!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.36,0:16:50.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Never... Never...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.47,0:16:55.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Of course, my father had\Nnothing to do with it,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.54,0:16:57.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but at around the same time,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.41,0:17:01.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,a massive amount of Dance Powder\Nwas found inside the palace...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.74,0:17:06.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They even had people\Nworking inside the palace?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.65,0:17:09.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's this road, Vivi-chan?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.69,0:17:15.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This was a canal that used to bring\Nwater in from the Sandora River.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.42,0:17:18.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Someone destroyed this canal, too...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.89,0:17:24.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,With its canal gone, the City of Green\Ncould no longer secure water.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.54,0:17:32.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,As if praying, the people continued\Nto wait, but rain never came.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.07,0:17:37.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ever since the Dance Powder incident,\Ndistrust in the king grows daily.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.18,0:17:40.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And it's all how Crocodile planned, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.25,0:17:44.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And then the fighting finally began.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.42,0:17:49.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,To escape the fighting, the\Nexhausted people abandoned the city
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.42,0:17:55.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and left for other oases\Nin search of water.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.40,0:17:58.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And then...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.80,0:18:06.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,the City of Green withered away.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.68,0:18:17.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,--Huh? Is that someone's voice?!\N--Is it the rebel army?!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.65,0:18:25.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't tell me Baroque Works\Nhas been following us!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.96,0:18:33.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,--No. It's just wind.\N--It has to be someone's voice!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.27,0:18:37.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's coming from all directions!\NWhat do we do, Big Brother?!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.87,0:18:39.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There's no danger.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.74,0:18:47.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's just wind blowing across the\Ntown and echoing off old buildings.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.42,0:18:49.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's as if...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.02,0:18:57.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's as if the city of\NErumalu is crying...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.09,0:19:07.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Here it comes!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.96,0:19:33.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Whoa, what was with that wind?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.00,0:19:34.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Someone's collapsed!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.00,0:19:43.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There are still people in this city?!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.14,0:19:50.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What did my father...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.75,0:19:54.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What did the citizens\Nof this country ever do?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.48,0:19:56.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,These people have worked\Nso hard to live,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.72,0:20:00.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,being natives of a desert land who\Nare forced to fight with nature.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.89,0:20:03.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yet he's destroyed their lives!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.16,0:20:06.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What gives him the right to do that?!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.00,0:20:09.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.50,0:20:13.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,All the while,\Nas one of the Seven Warlords,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.10,0:20:15.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,he pretends to be a hero of the people!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.47,0:20:21.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No one realizes he's\Ndeceiving the entire country!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.14,0:20:28.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Crocodile! Crocodile! Crocodile!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.59,0:20:30.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.49,0:20:38.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,can't let him get away with this!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.53,0:20:49.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Geez, you're all such kids.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.24,0:20:57.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Vivi!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:57.41,0:20:59.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's get moving!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:59.81,0:21:03.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm itching to do this now!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.82,0:21:06.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's go to Yuba!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.79,0:21:10.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's where the rebel army is, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.23,0:21:13.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. I'm going to persuade their\Nleader to stop the rebellion.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.00,0:21:15.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Persuade?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.40,0:21:19.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,All of Alabasta's calamities\Nare Crocodile's doing!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:19.20,0:21:20.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm going to tell him the truth
Dialogue: 0,0:21:20.60,0:21:22.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and have him stop the\Npointless shedding of blood!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.70,0:21:30.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Got it.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:46.19,0:21:52.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Like the adventurers\NI dreamed of when I was a child
Dialogue: 0,0:21:52.04,0:21:57.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I continue on to the ends of emotion
Dialogue: 0,0:21:57.11,0:22:03.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I scoop up my hands,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:03.08,0:22:09.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and the sand and time\Nthat spills from them
Dialogue: 0,0:22:09.72,0:22:16.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,show me that this is\Nwhat I was born to do
Dialogue: 0,0:22:16.73,0:22:24.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's continue swimming\Nat a near-tumbling speed
Dialogue: 0,0:22:28.84,0:22:36.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Until we wash up someday\Non a white sandy beach
Dialogue: 0,0:22:39.58,0:22:47.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,no one knows about
Dialogue: 0,0:22:56.40,0:22:58.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I can't go on...\NI can't take hot weather...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:58.67,0:23:00.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then take off that animal suit.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:00.07,0:23:02.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You jerk! Are you making\Nfun of reindeer?!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:02.34,0:23:04.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey. What in the world is Luffy doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:04.87,0:23:07.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,--He's riding a camel!\N--Wait! Something's chasing him!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:08.01,0:23:10.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ugh! How is he able to\Nsummon trouble like this?!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:10.88,0:23:12.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,On the next episode of One Piece!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:12.25,0:23:16.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"Adventure in the Country of Sand! The\NMonsters that Live in the Scorching Land"
Dialogue: 0,0:23:16.05,0:23:24.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm gonna be King of the Pirates!!
